VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT enable-oslogin\s*=\s*"FALSE"|enable-oslogin\s*=\s*"false"
WHEN EXPR PRESENT:enable-oslogin\s*=\s*"false"|enable-oslogin\s*=\s*false && MISSING:# intentional|# legacy|# migration
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects GCP instances with OS Login disabled, falling back to SSH key management.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for GCP VM with OS Login Disabled.
